#------------------------------------
#light scattering photometry (LSP)
        
#Light scattering photometers do not integrate the light from all scattered angles, but only view a portion of the available scattering angles. 
#Like nephelometry, it produces a bulk scattering coefficient of an air sample with similar time resolution and range. 
#In general they are calibrated with a standard test aerosol such as Arizona Test Dust, but typically these test aerosols have significantly different optical properties from real ambient air aerosols.
